text: Frits Mulder was a sailor from Belgium, who represented his country at the 1928 Summer Olympics in Amsterdam, Netherlands. Mulder, as crew member on the Belgian 6 Metre Ubu, took 5th place with helmsman A. J. J. Fridt and fellow crew members Ludovic Franck, Willy Van Rompaey and Arthur Sneyers. == Sources == * Category:Sailors at the 1928 Summer Olympics – 6 Metre Category:Olympic sailors of Belgium Category:Belgian male sailors (sport)
